      "**Stage 4: Tally Sync (TDL/XML Protocol)** — The AP Processor agent posts vouchers to Tally Prime using the native XML/TDL protocol. Tally doesn't have a REST API — it exposes a single HTTP endpoint that accepts XML envelopes containing TDL commands. Since Tally runs on the CA's local machine (not in the cloud), we built a bridge agent that tunnels requests through a WebSocket connection.",
      "## The Tally Bridge: Solving the On-Premise Problem",
